enetSMCConfigEntry.description: An entry in the enetSMC port table.

enetSMCConfigIndex.description: The value of the index uniquely specifies the physical port number to which this entry is applicable.

enetSMCConfigLineSpeed.name: enetSMCConfigLineSpeed
enetSMCConfigLineSpeed.description: The line speed configured for this adapter. Auto and 100 Mbit are only valid for the 9332 card.

enetSMCConfigInterface.name: enetSMCConfigInterface
enetSMCConfigInterface.description: This type of interface which is configured on this adapter. Setting the value to aui (1) is an invalid operation for interfaces which only support twistedPair or utp. Where: aui - Attachment Unit Interface, utp - Unshielded Twisted Pair.

enetSMCConfigMode.name: enetSMCConfigMode
enetSMCConfigMode.description: Indicates which duplex mode is configured on this interface.

enetSMCStatsIndex.name: enetSMCStatsIndex
enetSMCStatsIndex.description: The value of the index uniquely specifies the physical port number to which this entry is applicable.

enetSMCSQEErrors.name: enetSMCSQEErrors
enetSMCSQEErrors.description: The number of SQE/Heartbeat errors detected.

enetSMCRxMissedFrames.name: enetSMCRxMissedFrames
enetSMCRxMissedFrames.description: The number of receive frames missed because no buffers were available to accept the incoming data.

enetSMCRetries.description: Total number of transmission retries by this station on the attached LAN.

enetSMCRunts.description: Total number of runts detected on the attached LAN.

enetSMCFRAMorCRCErrors.name: enetSMCFRAMorCRCErrors
enetSMCFRAMorCRCErrors.description: Total number of Framing or CRC errors detected on LAN.

enetSMCTxDeferrals.name: enetSMCTxDeferrals
enetSMCTxDeferrals.description: The total number of TX deferrals encountered on the LAN segment.

enetSMCLateCollisions.name: enetSMCLateCollisions
enetSMCLateCollisions.description: Total number of late collisions encountered during transmission by this port.

enetSMCLossofCarrierErrors.name: enetSMCLossofCarrierErrors
enetSMCLossofCarrierErrors.description: Total number of loss of carrier errors encountered by this port.

enetSMCRetryErrors.name: enetSMCRetryErrors
enetSMCRetryErrors.description: Total number of TX retry limit errors encountered during transmission by this port.

enetSMCNoOfLinkResets.name: enetSMCNoOfLinkResets
enetSMCNoOfLinkResets.description: This is the number of link resets which have occurred since the last reinitialization of the unit.

enetSMCLastLinkResetReason.name: enetSMCLastLinkResetReason
enetSMCLastLinkResetReason.description: This object gives the reason code for the last reset which occurred on this LAN physical link. A value of noReason(1) is returned if the link has not reset. A value of management(2) is returned when a link reset has been caused by a management protocol (either SNMP or by LMS). A value of deviceReset(3) is returned if the link reset was caused by a hardware failure. A value of cableDrop(4) is returned when the link reset was caused by a missing or faulty cable.

enetSMCTimeSinceLastLinkReset.name: enetSMCTimeSinceLastLinkReset
enetSMCTimeSinceLastLinkReset.description: This is the time, in seconds, since the last link reset.

enetSMCRxPackets.name: enetSMCRxPackets
enetSMCRxPackets.description: This is the number of packets received on this link by the device driver.
